    Wand of The War Mage +1
    close
    s

    This wand appears to be carved from dragon bone.

    Requires attunement by an arcane magic user (Bard, Sorcerer, Warlock, Wizard, etc). 

    When attuned to the user, and used as a spell focus, this wand adds +1 to spell attack and spell DC, and the user's spell casting ability bonus adds to the damage inflicted by any spell or cantrip cast (minimum of +1) that has an attack roll or spell save.  This bonus damage applies once to each attack roll made or saving throw required. 


    Brazenthrone
    close
    s

    The Challenge

    Brazenthrone is infested with what has become of its former residents, which the Guard call Darkspawn.  Through the magic of Vaezis, the magic of Kongradol has been twisted to create these things that are neither alive nor dead.  They have occasionally broken out of the city, and the Guard have fought them and pushed them back, sealing them back inside. 

    From what the Guard knows, there are creatures that were once dwarves and some who were once elves.

    • The darkspawn regenerate, albeit slowly.  Fire or radiant damage slows this.
    • Bites from the darkspawn can cause the bitten to sicken and become darkspawn.
    • The elven darkspawn can drain life at a touch, and if all your life is drained you become darkspawn. Some are spellcasters.

    Ardulena believes that the Soulstone is the source of the Darkspawn's power - and so in all likelihood they will be drawn to it.

    Brazenthrone was once the home of tens of thousands of dwarves, and thousands of elves.


    The Task

    1. You must travel through Brazenthrone to the Underdark Outpost. There are two paths there:
      1. Through the Great Hall to the Gates in the NW wall - you will have to find a way through the Gates if they are sealed.
      2. Through a secret entrance somewhere in the ruins of the Old Palace - you will need to find it.
    2. Travel through the Underdark to Kongradol's Lair - the path to the north of the Outpost will take you there.
    3. Once in Kongradol's Lair, you will likely find her physical form. Bringing the Soulstone in proximity to her should open a portal to the Shadow Realm.
    4. Once in the Shadow Realm you will need to find where her soul is imprisoned - the Soulstone will guide you.
    5. Bringing the Soulstone to where her soul is trapped should break the magic binding her and free her of imprisonment.
    Link
    Clanggedin's Rage
    close
    s

    This magical greataxe requires attunement by a dwarf. It is inscribed with dwarven runes that read 'Clanggedin's Rage'.  It is a heavy, two-handed weapon with a +1 magical bonus to attack and damage and a base 3d6 slashing damage.

    The wielder can choose to enter a Berserk Rage as a bonus action and gain the following abilities:

    • You throw aside all concern for defense to attack with fierce desperation.  Doing so gives you advantage on your attack, but attack rolls against you have advantage until your rage ends.
    • You have advantage on Strength checks and saving throws.
    • You gain an additional +2 bonus to attack and damage due to your increased strength.
    • You have resistance to all damage.
    • You are unable to cast or concentrate on spells while raging.
    • You can make a single attack as a bonus action on each of your turns.

    The rage lasts for 1 minute. It ends early if you are knocked unconscious or if your turn ends and you haven’t attacked a hostile creature since your last turn or taken damage since then. You can also end your rage on your turn as a bonus action. 

    After using this ability the wielder's level of exhaustion increases by one, but you may recover all exhaustion points after a short rest.
